we are exposing the refreshToken , accessToken, resetPasswodToken by sending them in response.It is just for testing purpose. If you want to use in production , don't send them. refer auth.services.js

If you have frontend , then change the url from /api/auth/verify-email/:${token} to /verify-email/${token} . check for other methods too in common > config > email.js

thoroghly test the entire application before using in production.
